  "text": "The observable portion of TriplatinNC-A is extended along the backbone of one strand of the DDD (Sym 0 in Figure 3) . One Phosphate Clamp [Pt(b)] engages the O2P oxygen atom of C15 while the other [Pt(c)] engages the O2P atom of the adjacent G16 ( Figure 4 ). In contrast, in the DDD-TriplatinNC complex the PtN 4 units forms phosphate clamps with A17 and G16, but not with C15 [CITATION_1] . This difference in binding interactions may be due to the increased charge caused by the presence of the dangling hexanediamine, which forms hydrogen bonds with the O2P of G14 [CITATION_2] . This extra interaction appears to induce the trinuclear unit to bend, pushing the one PtN 4 coordination sphere away from the phosphate of C15, forming a total of three phosphate clamps.",
